---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<style>
  svg {
    padding: 0 1rem 1rem 0;
  }
  h2 {
    padding: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  /* ul {
    padding: 0;
  } */
  p {
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0;
  }
  .member-header-container {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .story-container {
    border-radius: 0;
  }
</style>

<Layout>
  <div class="opening-container">
    <div class="member-header-container">
      <div style="padding-bottom: 1rem;">
        <h2>Shoshana Freedman</h2>
        <h3>VP Sales and Purchasing</h3>
        <h3>Voted Loudest and Most Fun Employee</h3>
      </div>

      <svg width="10rem" height="10rem" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <circle cx="50%" cy="50%" r="4.8rem" fill="var(--guardian-green)"
        ></circle>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>In another life, I'm pretty sure I was a Princess.</li>
      <li>
        If I won the lottery tomorrow, I would go to a war-torn country and help
        people… but still show up to work Monday.
      </li>
      <li>
        The best piece of advice I've ever been given is: It’s better to be kind
        than right.
      </li>
      <li>If I could invent a holiday, it would involve food and family.</li>
      <li>
        What advice would you give a candidate who wants to join our team of
        superstars? Keep your sense of humor
      </li>
      <li>
        If I weren't so damn good at my job, I'd probably be an interior
        designer.
      </li>
      <li>Cats or dogs? Dogs.</li>
      <li>If I were a superhero, my superpower would be curing illnesses.</li>
      <li>When I was 5, I was pretty sure I'd be a lawyer</li>
      <li>
        Who is someone you admire, and why? Ruth Bader Ginsberg because of her
        strong sense of justice
      </li>
      <li>Name three words that you describe you. Impulsive, Funny, Giving</li>
      <li>
        How do you think your colleagues would describe you? Annoying but worth
        it
      </li>
      <li>
        What do you want to make sure you do before you die? Make a palpable
        difference in lives of the less fortunate
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="story-container">
    <div class="member-header-container">
      <svg width="10rem" height="10rem" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <circle cx="50%" cy="50%" r="4.8rem" fill="var(--guardian-green)"
        ></circle>
      </svg>
      <div style="padding-bottom: 1rem;  text-align: right">
        <h2>Thunder Dan</h2>
        <h3>Voice of Reason</h3>
        <h3>Guardian Medical’s Travelin’ Man</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>In another life, I'm pretty sure I was racecar driver.</li><li>
        If I won the lottery tomorrow, I'd start an indoor/outdoor athletic
        training facility. And, you know, keep working here.
      </li>
      <li>
        The best piece of advice I've ever been given is if you want something
        done, do it yourself.
      </li><li>
        If I could invent a holiday, it would involve hiking in the wilderness.
      </li><li>
        What advice would you give a candidate who wants to join our team of
        superstars? Be motivated and persistent.
      </li><li>
        If I weren't so damn good at my job, I'd probably be a couch potato.
      </li>
      <li>Cats or dogs? My dog’s name is Sophia. Enough said.</li>
      <li>My favorite word in the English language is faith.</li><li>
        My least favorite word that has no direct English translation is THAT.
        It should be removed from the English language.
      </li>
      <li>
        What's the most inspiring part of your job? I am helping others with a
        solution to a problem.
      </li><li>
        The most important thing I learned before high school was it costs
        nothing to be kind.
      </li><li>
        If I were a superhero, my superpower would be I could be in two places
        at one time.
      </li>
      <li>
        When I was 5, I was pretty sure I'd be a clerk at Lawson’s for the free
        candy when I grew up.
      </li><li>
        Who is someone you admire, and why? I admire my grandmother for leaving
        her hometown of Donegal, Ireland.
      </li><li>
        Name three words that you describe you. Honest, reliable, friendly
      </li><li>
        How do you think your colleagues would describe you? Hard working and
        fun.
      </li><li>
        What do you want to make sure you do before you die? Travel to Italy
        with my family.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="opening-container">
    <div class="member-header-container">
      <div style="padding-bottom: 1rem;">
        <h2>Brandt Butze</h2>
        <h3>Company Cheerleader</h3>
        <h3>Sometimes Grumpiest Man at Work</h3>
      </div>

      <svg width="10rem" height="10rem" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <circle cx="50%" cy="50%" r="4.8rem" fill="var(--guardian-green)"
        ></circle>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>
        1. In another life, I'm pretty sure I was introverted as I am NOT that
        way in this life.
      </li>
      <li>
        2. If I won the lottery tomorrow, I’d donate a lot of money to helping
        families afflicted by cancer. And, you know, keep working here.
      </li>
      <li>
        The best piece of advice I've ever been given is to be part of the
        solution.
      </li>
      <li>
        If I could invent a holiday, it would involve an aluminum pole, and the
        airing of grievances. Wait, Seinfeld beat me to it. FESTIVUS for the
        rest of us!
      </li>
      <li>
        What advice would you give a candidate who wants to join our team of
        superstars? Balance life and work.
      </li>
      <li>
        If I weren't so damn good at my job, I'd probably be a writer. I would
        say “If I were so damn good at writing I’d probably be doing that.
      </li>
      <li>
        Cats or dogs? Dogs. Not that you must choose, but cats scare the hell
        out of me.
      </li>
      <li>
        The most important thing I learned before high school was that my world
        around me is very small.
      </li>
      <li>If I were a superhero, my superpower would be EMPATHY.</li>
      <li>
        When I was 5, I was pretty sure I'd be a professional hockey player when
        I grew up.
      </li>
      <li>
        Who is someone you admire, and why? My daughter, Ana. She (we) lost her
        brother to cancer. Ana graduated high school and moved to Chicago to
        college. Her strength and love know no bounds.
      </li>
      <li>Name three words that you describe you. Empathetic, Loving, Funny</li>
      <li>How do you think your colleagues would describe you? Loud</li>
      <li>
        What do you want to make sure you do before you die? Live every moment
        with compassion and love.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
